Except as provided in paragraph (6) of this subsection, the practical experience shall be documented by the permittee on the forms provided by the Department and submitted to the Department on a monthly basis when engaging in practical experience. The forms shall include:
Number of days spent gaining practical experience under the presence of a tidal fish licensee;
Particular fishing activities;
The signature of a tidal fish licensee certifying that the recorded information regarding the practical experience in fishing activities is true and correct; and
Copies of appropriate income tax forms documenting the permittee's compensated employment in the presence of a tidal fish licensee.

This paragraph shall apply only to an individual who:
Served as a crew member to a tidal fish licensee or a person that holds a commercial fishing license issued by another state or the federal government;
Held a Maryland Provisional Chesapeake Bay Charter Boat Permit in accordance with § 4-210.2 of this title;
Held a tidal fish license and has not permanently transferred a tidal fish license within the past 24 months in accordance with § 4-701(j) of this subtitle;
Held a temporary transfer of a tidal fish license;
Harvested fish from the waters of the Exclusive Economic Zone and landed the fish in the State;
Holds a commercial fishing license issued by another state or the federal government; or
Held a commercial fishing license issued by another state or the federal government.
